cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CR

The paper focuses on image and video analytics, specifically face detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for training also suggests machine learning (cs.MM) as a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the need to save computational resources, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of HEVC bitstreams for face detection could also fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
